06/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The European Commission, EBRD and Greece's Global Finance announced on Thursday (5 June) the establishment of a fund for investment in small- and medium-sized businesses in Romania and Bulgaria. The partners allocated 16.5m euros to cover two-thirds of the investment projects; private companies will secure the rest. The fund will target companies with up to 250 employees and no more than 40m euros in sales. (Standart - 06/06/03; BTA - 05/06/03)
